{[#] White to move} 12. c5 {changing structure, now we will play for the
queenside majority. It's important to note that for Black is very difficult to
play e7-e5} Qd7 13. Nf3 a5 14. Rc1 $14 {We have reached a fighting position,
where White has the more pleasant side. he can continue with moves like
Qc2-Ne5-Nd3 and slowly prepare a3-b4-b5. It will not be easy, but from the
other side, Black doesn't have a clear plan to prevent White from expanding on
the queenside.} *

